annotation.TEXT: The bullets on the nonspells are closer together this time. Hopefully you can find wide enough openings to slip through when necessary.
How will I do with the final gauntlet?
As long as I remember that this spell is coming, I can avoid having a lot of trouble with it.
Perfect! Now for another fairly easy nonspell!

Oh, yeah. There's this "last spell". Occasionally I fail it, but at least I know I won't spend more than one "bomb" if I fail it (unlike with some other patterns, which could be really costly if I royally screw up).
Now, for the third nonspell on Lunatic, I discovered something... Move to the bottom center and stand perfectly still.
Awesome, now for the boss...
Nuts. I let two FOEs escape. So, that cost me... probably one small power item and one point item? Eh, I'll live.
This huge group of FOEs coming up might be tricky...
Okay! And I'm fully recovered, just like that!
Sweet! That went very well!
Okay, don't panic. There's a way out of this, I know it!
First spell is about the same, but the spread is larger. Still shouldn't be difficult.
Oh, god... This guy again.
Yes, that's right, a much needed "Icicle Fall -Easy" style safe spot! I have never been hit while standing still down here on this one particular nonspell!
Second nonspell, and it's even faster than before...
Uh, oh. That was unexpected! But, at least the game game me a break there!
The nonspells are a bit trickier this time, but should be well within my capability to handle.
Okay, so even if I do know that spell is coming and do the diversion thing, sometimes the bullets move in such a way as to restrict my movements anyway. Yeah, it's tough (unlike this nonspell).
Alright, I'm at full power! Now power items will decrease the right number of "Point" much faster!
Okay, the right number of "Point" is back to 100, so I've fully recovered from failing that "last spell". (Of course, I'd have more points if I'd captured it, but oh, well...)
And on this difficulty, I'm grazing 329 bullets per wave! However, I'm not going to loiter around on this spell forever.
This spell is just like before. Just slip between the bullets that come your way.
And that's game! Wow, look at that score!

Well, there's probably not going to be much for me to say during parts of this run, so don't expect nearly as many annotations as in my first episode of this game! (Also, this'll be easier on me too. I don't want to take all day annotating!)
Well, he seems to like lingering just outside of my range, but I'll be patient and wait. (At worst, I'll just time out the nonspell.)
Whoa! I just passed my old high score, and I'm not even done with the game yet!
Okay, it's the second spell of this boss, so do that diversion thing!
It's still not extremely difficult, though.
Second nonspell, just as easy, yada yada.
The Simple Gimmick's planets have many more satellites surrounding them this time. Still, the same strategy as before should work.
Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Lunatic on Project Nize Festival!

Also, here's another thing I didn't show before. You can select to play as just one member of a team (just like in IN) by holding C or Shift and then pressing Z. I don't know if there are any special requirements that need to be fulfilled first, though.
Why, I'm going to go Lunatic!
Alright, it's final boss time! Her nonspells are still almost a joke for this point in the game. She does launch an extra ring of amulets that moves fast, but it's still easy to dodge.
Sweet! And I've capped my point item value! Also, my bombs back there were only on nonspells, so I did capture every spell card in this stage!
Watch out for the fast shots that the fairies shoot in this stage.
Well, that could've gone better, but it also could've been a lot worse!
Okay, third spell, and this one is kind of tricky, and sometimes I have to bomb on it, but I'd really rather avoid bombing if at all possible!

Okay, good enough. I'm glad I only needed one bomb for that insane nonspell. Now for something more sane. As usual, move behind the boss during the phase out, then circle back to the front during the phase in.
Now, just like before, get off the bottom of the screen here. However, on Hard and Lunatic, the boss launches shots as well, making this one very tricky!
Sometimes I like to divert the first set of large balls on these nonspells like this. I'm not sure if it's extremely helpful, though.
Hello, and welcome back to Project Nize Festival yet again! So what am I going to do this time around?

Yeah, that's freaky! Also, I got into a tight spot on the right, but that was better than being down below with the dancing lasers! (Feel free to back up the video and watch this spell again if you want.)
Likewise, this Remilia-like character's "barrels of doom" are only locked in place while focusing as well. Otherwise, the "barrels" stay with the player while unfocused.
Huh. I guess they didn't have much about. Alright, now this guy's nonspells are much trickier, as the bullets coming from the large red balls are much closer together. Watch out.

For the "last spell", you better believe I'm making use of the blind spot! (Good thing this isn't the other stage 4 boss, whose similar-looking "last spell" can't actually be exploited this way due to the bullets speeding up when you get close!)
On top of that, on Lunatic, there are all these extra red bullets to worry about. Fun.
Nice! However, there's still more to deal with...
Oh, well. Let's move on and try to recover from that slip up.
The second "last spell" is a bit trickier. The bullets' higher speed makes it tougher to find a safe spot in time.
Fourth nonspell, and it's still suprisingly easy.
And by some miracle, I captured that spell and pulled off a perfect stage 3! Now, what about stage 4?
There's a lot more bullets, but that just means more graze for you! Also, try to finish off the spell when lots of bullets are on the screen, to get many more points!
Okay, now with this spell, the yellow shots are still aimed, but they spread out more, making them tougher to dodge.
Fourth 1-up at 190 million.
It totally blew away that 1.35-whatever billion score that I had before!

Darn, I'm just 0.05 short of the 4.00 power mark. (I think I would've had it if I got the large power up first in that previous group, but I was already in the autocollect zone, so I couldn't aim for it.)
It's hard to tell, but I think the ninth 1-up occurred at 1.29 billion there.
Nuts! Screwed that up!

The main trickiness has to do with the bullets' speed while they're phased in. I definitely want to move towards the upper third of the screen during the phase out, so I have plenty of room to back up during the phase in.
First spell. She moves around during this spell on Lunatic, eliminating many safe spots from the lower difficulties, but the Russia-sized safe spot above her still exists!
And now for the stage 4 artificial boss.
...and I screwed up right out the door on it! Let's try to keep these mistakes to a minimum!
Now, for the most part, this guy's nonspells are the most dangerous part of this fight on Lunatic! But, the first one shouldn't be too tough...
Good, and I got my fifth 1-up at 330 million.
Full power mode! (Too bad it doesn't come with a bullet cancelling effect like in Touhou games 4 through 8.)
And now, for the final five "last spells"! The first one's a joke, just like usual.

That was almost dangerous! Anyway, for this spell, get off the bottom of the screen as usual, but don't go looking for a Nevada-sized safe spot this time. On Hard and Lunatic, extra bullets coming at another angle remove that safe spot.
Although, there are a lot more lasers, but that doesn't really make it much harder unless you move around like a mad man while they're spawning.
Fifth spell, move in very close during the phase out and back off slowly during the phase in. I'm glad this guy's spells generally aren't as nasty as his nonspells!
Okay, now with this spell, on Hard and Lunatic, the yellow shots actually aim at you, and they appear to change course slightly during their flight paths one time, so watch out for that!

Woo, second 1-up at 30 million (the first 1-up was at 10 million). I'm going to score much higher in this game than in the first video, since I'm on Lunatic, so I'll try to announce each 1-up mark as I hit them from now on.
Sixth 1-up at 510 million, and now my lives are capped!
Actually, this nonspell still seems easy!
Whoa! Close call there! I often have close calls on this spell, but I usually capture it for some reason, despite how tricky it looks!
The "last spell" strategy here is the same as well. Just keep tap dodging to avoid the bullets that are spawning just above you.
Fifth spell. Once again, very tricky to dodge, but her HP isn't any higher on this spell, meaning it should be over with quickly.
There we go, finally! (I swear, she did that on purpose!)
Yes! A perfect stage 2! Can I do the same for stage 3? Maybe, but the "last spell" there is probably going to screw me over, but let's wait until I actually get to that to worry about it.
ARGH!!! Failed it... I'm inconsistent at that one...
Her second spell is very tricky once again. I'm going to try to circle around her at the right rate of speed like before...
Oh, I'm going to stage 6B, definitely!
Oh, good. I made it to a spell card. Now I can breathe easy for a moment. The basic strategy on this spell card is still the same, by the way.
And there goes all of my power again. I wonder why these particular "last spells" were designed this way... At least I got my lost life back at 1.63 billion points (the tenth 1-up).
First spell, same as before, although there's a lot more than two aimed bullets now, but it's nothing ridiculous.
Still not exactly a challenging nonspell...

Now, I did show you guys the Hard version of this spell at the end of episode two in spell card practice. The same strategy applies here, but squeezing through the gaps in between the red shots is harder.
That was close. Now, for this spell, same deal as before. Stand still at the bottom, then tap dodge at the last moment and graze. Easy!
Alright, there we go! 4.00 power is when the "barrels of doom" start firing really rapidly, and give you the best DPS in the game!
However, once you're in a safe spot, there's nothing more to do but sit and wait (and perhaps keep shooting at the boss for slightly more points I guess).
Fourth nonspell, and I'd say this one rivals Mokou's eighth nonspell in IN! Having to bomb here is almost guaranteed!
Graze farming! Just be sure to back away in time to find an opening for the bullets' phase in!
And now I'm fully recovered on the "Point" value. Actually, that's getting pretty high. I should be able to cap the left number at 9999 soon if I don't screw up a lot.
Now, most characters still perform as you'd expect while solo, but just like in IN, the Youmu-like character can lock the familiar's aim in a particular direction while focusing.
Now, this "last spell" gets really fast on Lunatic...
Oh, come on!
Same deal as before here. Just dodge the bullets that come your way.

Fortunately, since I could win by damaging the boss this time, I didn't have to deal with the spell for very long, and as such, didn't have to watch out for the additional ring of tiny bullets during the spell!
ALWAYS move to the lower-left quadrant during the break in the amulet lines, or you're probably boned!
Third spell, which is shared with the other stage 4 boss. Shouldn't be too difficult if I pay attention and keep moving to dodge the wider aimed amulet spreads.
Okay, final "last spell"! Same as before, move about halfway between the bottom of the screen and the boss, and just dodge some slower bullets that come your way.
Okay, now watch the lasers that hit the bottom of the screen here.
Also, it's great for graze farming if you move with her very carefully!

Okay, now it's time to worry about this "last spell"! You still gotta dodge the random bullets and spinning lasers, but on Lunatic, there's a very high chance of lasers glitching out and doing very weird things that'll screw you over!
WARNING! Huge number of FOEs approaching!
Seventh 1-up at 730 million. Now, if I'm gonna bomb here, I want the bomb to go up the center, to protect me more, and hopefully hit the boss and end the nonspell faster.
Too bad my power dropped below 4.00, so this'll take longer than usual.
Huh. The third 1-up was at 90 million this time. Anyway, this spell could get tricky. The strategy is the same, but the bullets are faster, as usual.
Yeah, I'm bombing here. Hopefully, one regular bomb is all I'll need.
Fourth spell, "Concept". Same strategy as last time. It's just that the bullets are more plentiful as usual, but it's nothing ridiculous.
This might actually be trickier than it looks, as you have to be careful not to move too far with each tap.
Nuts! I really shouldn't have gotten hit by that...
The bullets move faster, but does that really mean anything?
This spell is about the same as before, but faster, and the V-spreads are wider, so keep that in mind.
Third spell, and guess what I'm doing once again!
Big group of FOEs coming here, but I should be able to handle them.
Watch out for "moons" that break orbit and go wherever as their planets leave the screen. This is more likely on Lunatic.
I'm not at 4.00 power, and she's not always in the line of fire of my "barrels of doom", so this'll take a while...

And as far as I can tell, this safe spot only exists on his third nonspell of Lunatic, and doesn't work on any of his other nonspells or on any other difficulty. (However, if anyone finds out that I'm wrong about that, let me know!)
And there goes all of my power (not just a 1.00 subtraction).
Well, I guess it didn't take that long. Alright, I'm doing very well, having only failed two spells so far. That's better than usual for me by this point!
For this game, I'm going to use the right character of team Maribel Han alone. (Does that mean I'm playing as Han solo?)
Crazy through! ...Which was probably unnecessary.
D'oh! Don't panic! I can recover! (Also, eighth 1-up at 990 million, followed immediately by me reaching the billion mark!)

Oy, I'm glad that other spell is over. Now, for the fourth "last spell", there's a twist on Lunatic... The lines of dark bullets are actually aimed away from you! You still have to tap dodge to avoid the tiny white bullets, though, but don't crash into the dark bullets by mistake!
Oh, watch out for those bullets! As you'd expect, the enemies on Lunatic are going to generally launch a lot more bullets at you! This could be great for graze if you know what you're doing, though!
Her third "last spell" is by far the hardest. I usually fail it, and I really wish I could access it in spell card practice.
This spell is just like before, but the aimed shots are more frequent, and you have to dodge around some other shots too. Still shouldn't be too hard.
Now I've gotta figure out which Touhou flash game I should make a video of next... (This flash game will be hard to top!)
And with a second hit, I lose a life, along with 10% of my "Point" value. Nuts!
Alright, it's boss time! Now, Now Learning has an additional nonspell and spell on Hard and Lunatic. The extra nonspell isn't anything special, but the extra spell could be tricky!
Alright, let's clobber some fairies and get my power back!
Okay, I've been doing well on these large FOE groups in the past...
